obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (46653)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title Title.
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for Part B States.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46653&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Court-fees Act, 1870.`
  line
  line `Extent of Act. -- It extends to the whole of India except ^1[the territories which, immediately before`
  line `the 1st November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States];`
  line
  line `Commencement of Act. -- And it shall come into force on the first day of April, 1870.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_a:
  sectionId (46654)
  sectionNo 1A
  orderNo 2
  title `Definition of “appropriate Government”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46654&sectionno=1A&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[1A. Definition of "appropriate Government"."In this Act the appropriate Government`
  line `means, in relation to fees or stamps relating to documents presented or to be presented before any`
  line `officer serving under the Central Government, that Government, and in relation to any other fees`
  line `or stamps, the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (46655)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 3
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46655&sectionno=2&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1 ["Chief Controlling Revenue-authority" defined.] Rep. by the A. O. 1937.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act (7 of 1870).--For section 2 of the Court Fees Act, 1870, hereinafter`
  line `called the principal Act, the following section shall be substituted:--`
  line
  line `"2. Definition.--In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(1) 'appeal' includes a cross objection;`
  line
  line `(2) 'suit' includes an appeal from a decree except in section 8-A."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The s. 2 relating to repeal of enactments was rep. by the Repealing Act, 1870 (14 of 1870). A section defining Chief Controlling`
  line `Revenue-authority was added by s. 2 of the Court-fees (Amendment) Act, 1901 (10 of 1901), and was slightly amended by the`
  line `Repealing and Amending Act, 1917 (24 of 1917). For the definition of the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority see now the`
  line `General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), s. 3(10).`
  line `The A.O. 1937 rep. s. 2 as in force elsewhere than in Bengal. In that Province the section subs. by the Court-fees (Bengal`
  line `Amendment) Act, 1935 (Ben. 7 of 1935), s. 3 contains definitions of appeal, Chief Controlling Revenue-authority,`
  line `Collector and Suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46656)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Levy of fees in High Courts on their original sides.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46656&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The fees payable for the time being to the`
  line `clerks and officers (other than the Sheriffs and attorneys) of ^1`
  line `[the ^2`
  line `[High Courts other than those of`
  line `Kerala, Mysore and Rajasthan]],`
  line
  line `or chargeable in each of such Courts under No. 11 of the first, and Nos. 7, 12, 14,^3`
  line ***
  line `20 and 21 of the second, schedule to this Act annexed;`
  line
  line `Levy of fees in Presidency Small Cause Courts.—and the fees for the time being chargeable in the`
  line `Courts of Small Causes at the ^4`
  line `presidency-towns, and their several offices;`
  line
  line `shall be collected in manner hereinafter appearing.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by the A.O.1950, for "the Courts which are High Courts for the purposes of the Government of India Act, 1935".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "High Courts for Part A States".`
  line
  line `3. The number "16" rep. by Act 12 of 1891.`
  line
  line `4. See the Presidency Small Cause Courts Act, 1882 (15 of 1882), Ch. X.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46657)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Fees on documents filed, etc., in High Courts in their extraordinary jurisdiction. In their appellate jurisdiction. As courts of reference and revision`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1922, s. 2, for "judgment of two".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46657&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line No
  line `document of any of the kinds specified in the first or second schedule to this Act annexed, as chargeable`
  line `with fees, shall be filed, exhibited or recorded in, or shall be received or furnished by, any of the said`
  line `High Courts in any case coming before such Court in the exercise of its extraordinary original civil`
  line jurisdiction;
  line
  line `or in the exercise of its extraordinary original criminal jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `In their appellate jurisdiction.or in the exercise of its jurisdiction as regards appeals from the`
  line `^1[judgments (other than judgments passed in the exercise of the ordinary original civil jurisdiction of the`
  line `Court) of one] or more Judges of the said Court, or of a Division Court;`
  line
  line `or in the exercise of its jurisdiction as regards appeals from the Courts subject to its superintendence;`
  line
  line `As Courts of reference and revision.or in the exercise of its jurisdiction as a Court of reference or`
  line revision;
  line
  line `unless in respect of such document there be paid a fee of an amount not less than that indicated by`
  line `either of the said schedules as the proper fee for such document.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 4 of Act VII of 1870.--In the marginal heading to the first clause of`
  line `section 4 of the Court Fees Act, 1870, as amended from time to time in its application to Uttar Pradesh for`
  line `the words "in the High Courts in their ordinary or extraordinary jurisdiction" shall be substitution.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act X of 1959, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 4 of Act VII of 1870.--In section 4 of the Court Fees Act, 1870, as amended`
  line `from time to time in its application to Uttar Pradesh--`
  line
  line `(1) for the words "any of the said High Courts", the words "the High Court of Judicature at`
  line `Allahabad shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(2) between the words "in the exercise of its" and the words "extraordinary original civil`
  line `jurisdiction", the words "ordinary or" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(3) between the words "in the exercise of its" and the words "extraordinary original criminal`
  line `jurisdiction", the words "ordinary or" shall be inserted; and`
  line
  line `(4) after the sub-paragraph "or in the exercise of its jurisdiction as a Court of reference or`
  line `revision", the following sub-paragraphs shall be added--`
  line
  line `"Or in the exercise of its jurisdiction to issue direction the exercise of nation, orders or writs`
  line `under the jurisdiction to issue Constitution of India;`
  line
  line `Or in the exercise of jurisdiction in any other in the exercise of any other jurisdiction matter."`
  line
  line `"Vide Uttar Pradesh Act X of 1959, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46658)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Procedure in case of difference as to necessity or amount of fee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46658&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `When any difference arises`
  line `between the officer whose duty it is to see that any fee is paid under this Chapter and any suitor or`
  line `attorney, as to the necessity of paying a fee or the amount thereof, the question shall, when the difference`
  line `arises in any of the said High Courts, be referred to the taxing-officer, whose decision thereon shall be`
  line `final, except when the question is, in his opinion, one of general importance, in which case he shall refer`
  line `it to the final decision of the Chief Justice of such High Court, or of such Judge of the High Court as the`
  line `Chief Justice shall appoint either generally or specially in this behalf.`
  line
  line `When any such difference arises in any of the said Courts of Small Causes, the question shall be`
  line `referred to the Clerk of the Court, whose decision thereon shall be final, except when the question is, in`
  line `his opinion, one of general importance, in which case he shall refer it to the final decision of the first`
  line `Judge of such Court.`
  line
  line `The Chief Justice shall declare who shall be taxing-officer within the meaning of the first paragraph`
  line `of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46659)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Fees on documents filed, etc., in Mofussil Courts or in public offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46659&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Except in the`
  line `Court hereinbefore mentioned, no document of any of the kinds specified as chargeable in the first`
  line `or second schedule to this Act annexed shall be filed, exhibited or recorded in any Court of Justice,`
  line `or shall be received or furnished by any public officer, unless in respect of such document there be`
  line `paid a fee of an amount not less than that indicated by either of the said schedules as the proper fee`
  line `for such document.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 6 of Act (7 of 1870).--Section 6 of the principal Act shall be re-numbered as`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 6 and , after the said sub-section, the following sub-section shall be inserted:--`
  line
  line `"(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Provincial Government may, by`
  line `notification, direct that a copy of a document, specified as chargeable in Schedules I and II to this`
  line `Act annexed, shall be furnished by a public officer without payment of the fee indicated by either of`
  line `the said Schedules as the proper fee for such copy and the copy so furnished shall be chargeable`
  line `with the requisite fee only when it is filed, exhibited or recorded in any Court of justice or received`
  line `by a public officer as mentioned in sub-section (1)."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 4]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 6 of Act (7 of 1870).--In section 6 of the Court Fees Act, 1870 as`
  line `amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh, hereinafter, in this Chapter referred to as the principal`
  line Act,--
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), in the first proviso, for the words "the United Provinces Tenancy Act,`
  line `1939, or the United Provinces Land Revenue Act, 1901", the words "any law relation to land`
  line `tenures or land revenue shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (6), for the words "Chief Inspector of Stamps" the words "Commission of`
  line `Stamps" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 6 of 1980, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 6-A.--In section 6-A of the principal Act, in sub-section (3), for the`
  line `words "Chief Inspector of Stamps", the words "Commissioners of Stamps" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 6 of 1980, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 6-B.--In section 6-B of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), for the`
  line `words "Chief Inspector of Stamps", the words "Commissioner of Stamps" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 6 of 1980, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46660)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Computation of fees payable in certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46660&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The amount of fee payable under this Act in the`
  line `suits next hereinafter mentioned shall be computed as follows:`
  line
  line `for money.--(i) In suits for money (including suits for damages or compensation, or arrears of`
  line `maintenance, of annuities, or of other sums payable periodically)according to the amount claimed.`
  line
  line `for maintenance and annuities.--(ii) In suits for maintenance and annuities or other sums`
  line `payable periodicallyaccording to the value of the subject-matter of the suit, and such value shall be`
  line `deemed to be ten times the amount claimed to be payable for one year:`
  line
  line `for other movable property having a market-value. (iii) In suits for movable property other`
  line `than money, where the subject-matter has a market-valueaccording to such value at the date of`
  line `presenting the plaint;`
  line
  line `(iv) In suits---`
  line
  line `for movable property of no market-value.--(a) for movable property where the subjectmatter has no market-value, as, for instance, in the case of documents relating to title,`
  line
  line `to enforce a right to share in joint family property.--(b) to enforce the right to share in`
  line `any property on the ground that it is joint family property,`
  line
  line `for a declaratory decree and consequential relief.--(c) to obtain a declaratory decree or`
  line `order, where consequential relief is prayed,`
  line
  line `for an injunction.(d) to obtain an injunction,`
  line
  line `for easements.--(e) for a right to some benefit (not herein otherwise provided for) to arise`
  line `out of land, and`
  line
  line `for accounts.--(f) for accounts--`
  line
  line `according to the amount at which the relief sought is valued in the plaint or memorandum`
  line `of appeal :`
  line
  line `In all such suits the plaintiff shall state the amount at which he values the relief sought`
  line `^1***:`
  line
  line `for possession of land, houses and gardens.--(v) In suits for the possession of land, houses and`
  line `gardensaccording to the value of the subject-matter; and such value shall be deemed to be`
  line
  line `where the subject-matter is land, and--`
  line
  line `(a) where the land forms an entire estate, or a definite share of an estate, paying annual`
  line `revenue to Government,`
  line
  line `or forms part of such an estate and is recorded in the Collector's register as separately`
  line `assessed with such revenue,`
  line
  line `and such revenue is permanently settled--`
  line
  line `ten times the revenue so payable:`
  line
  line `(b) where the land forms an entire estate, or a definite share of an estate, paying annual`
  line `revenue to Government, or forms part of such estate and is recorded as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `and such revenue is settled, but not permanently---`
  line
  line `five times the revenue so payable:`
  line
  line `(c) where the land pays no such revenue, or has been partially exempted from such payment, or is`
  line `charged with any fixed payment in lieu of such revenue,`
  line
  line `and nett profits have arisen from the land during the year next before the date of presenting the plaint`
  line
  line `fifteen times such nett profits:`
  line
  line `but where no such nett profits have arisen therefromthe amount at which the Court shall`
  line `estimate the land with reference to the value of similar land in the neighbourhood :`
  line
  line `(d) where the land forms part of an estate paying revenue to Government, but is not a definite`
  line `share of such estate and is not separately assessed as above-mentionedthe market-value of the land:`
  line
  line `Proviso as to Bombay Presidency.--Provided that, in the ^2territories subject to the Governor of`
  line `Bombay in Council, the value of the land shall be deemed to be`
  line
  line `(1) where the land is held on settlement for a period not exceeding thirty years and pays the`
  line `full assessment to Governmenta sum equal to five times the survey-assessment;`
  line
  line `(2) where the land is held on a permanent settlement, or on a settlement for any period`
  line `exceeding thirty years, and pays the full assessment to Governmenta sum equal to ten times the`
  line `survey-assessment; and`
  line
  line `(3) where the whole or any part of the annual survey-assessment is remitteda sum`
  line `computed under paragraph (1) or paragraph (2) of this proviso, as the case may be, in`
  line `addition to ten times the assessment, or the portion of assessment, so remitted;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The word estate, as used in this paragraph, means any land subject to the`
  line `payment of revenue, for which the proprietor or a farmer or raiyat shall have executed a separate`
  line `engagement to Government, or which, in the absence of such engagement, shall have been separately`
  line `assessed with revenue:`
  line
  line `for houses and gardens.-- (e) Where the subject-matter is a house or garden according to the`
  line `market-value of the house or garden:`
  line
  line `to enforce a right of pre-emption.--(vi) In suits to enforce a right of pre-emption-according to the`
  line `value (computed in accordance with paragraph (v) of this section) of the land, house or garden in respect`
  line `of which the right is claimed:`
  line
  line `for interest of assignee of land revenue.(vii) In suits for the interest of an assignee of land`
  line `revenuefifteen times his nett profits as such for the year next before the date of presenting the plaint;`
  line
  line `to set aside an attachment.--(viii) In suits to set aside an attachment of land or of an interest in land`
  line `or revenueaccording to the amount for which the land or interest was attached:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where such amount exceeds the value of the land or interest, the amount of fee shall be`
  line `computed as if the suit were for the possession of such land or interest.`
  line
  line `to redeem.--(ix) In suits against a mortgagee for the recovery of the property mortgaged,`
  line
  line `to foreclose.and in suits by a mortgagee to foreclose the mortgage, or, where the mortgage is made`
  line `by conditional sale, to have the sale declared absolute`
  line
  line `according to the principal money expressed to be secured by the instrument of mortgage :`
  line
  line `for specific performance.--(x) In suits for specific performance`
  line
  line `(a) of a contract of saleaccording to the amount of the consideration :`
  line
  line `(b) of a contract of mortgageaccording to the amount agreed to be secured :`
  line
  line `(c) of a contract of leaseaccording to the aggregate amount of the fine or premium (if any) and`
  line
  line `of the rent agreed to be paid during the first year of the term :`
  line
  line `(d) of an awardaccording to the amount or value of the property in dispute :`
  line
  line `between landlord and tenant.(xi) In the following suits between landlord and tenant:--`
  line
  line `(a) for the delivery by a tenant of the counterpart of a lease,`
  line
  line `(b) to enhance the rent of a tenant having a right of occupancy,`
  line
  line `(c) for the delivery by a landlord of a lease,`
  line
  line `^3[(cc) for the recovery of immovable property from a tenant, including a tenant holding over after`
  line `the determination of a tenancy,]`
  line
  line `(d) to contest a notice of ejectment,`
  line
  line `(e) to recover the occupancy of ^4[immovable property] from which a tenant has been illegally`
  line `ejected by the landlord, and`
  line
  line `(f) for abatement of rent`
  line
  line `according to the amount of the rent of the ^4[immovable property] to which the suit refers,`
  line `payable for the year next before the date of presenting the plaint.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 7 of Act (7 of 1870).--In section 7 of the principal Act, for the words "in the`
  line `suits next hereinafter mentioned" the words "in the suits next hereinafter mentioned except suits for relief`
  line `under section 14 of the Religious Endowments Act, 1863, or under section 91 or section 92 of the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908", shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 7ii of Act (7 of 1870).--In section 7ii of the principal Act, after the words`
  line `"shall be deemed to be the words " "in suits for maintenance five times and in other suits " shall be`
  line inserted.
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 6]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 7iv of Act (7 of 1870).--Clause (b) of section 7iv of the principal Act shall`
  line `be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 7]`
  line
  line `Insertion new paragraph in section 7 of Act (7 of 1870).--In section 7 of the principal Act after`
  line `paragraph iv the following paragraph shall be inserted:--`
  line
  line `"iv-A. in a suit for cancellation of a decree for money or other property having a money --value,`
  line `or other document securing money or other property having such value,`
  line
  line `According to the value of the subject-matter of the suit, and such value shall be deemed to be--`
  line
  line `if the whole decree or other document is sought to be cancelled, the amount or the value`
  line `of the property for which the decree was passed or the other document executed,`
  line
  line `if a part of the decree or other document is sought to be cancelled, such part of the`
  line `amount or value of the property.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In any case where a suit for the cancellation of a whole decree for money`
  line `or other property having a money value, or other document securing money or other property having`
  line `such value has to be instituted, but the substantial relief claimed is only in respect of a part of the`
  line `amount or the decree was passed or the other document as executed, the value of the subject matter of`
  line `the suit shall be deemed to be such part of the amount or value of the property in respect of which the`
  line `relief is sought."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 8]`
  line
  line `Amendment paragraph v of section 7 of Act (7 of 1870).--In paragraph v of section 7 of the`
  line `principal Act,`
  line
  line `(1) in clause (a), for the word "ten" the word "ten" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(2) in clause (b), for the word "five" the word "ten" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(3) the following proviso shall be inserted after the existing proviso:--`
  line
  line `"Provided further that in suits for possession of land if rules are framed under section 3 of the`
  line `Suits Valuation Act, 1887 (7 of 1887), for determining the value for the purposes of jurisdiction, the`
  line `value so determined shall be deemed to be the value of the hand for the purposes of this paragraph ;`
  line and
  line
  line `(4) the existing Explanation shall be re-numbered as Explanation I, and, after the`
  line `Explanation so re-numbered, the following Explanation shall be added, namely:`
  line
  line `"Explanation II.--In this paragraph, 'building' includes a house, out-house, stable, privy, urinal,`
  line `shed, hut, wall, and any other such structure, whether of masonry, bricks, wood, mud, metal or any`
  line `other material whatsoever."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 9]`
  line
  line `Insertion of new paragraph vi-A in section 7 of Act (7 of 1870).--In section 7 of the principal Act`
  line `after paragraph vi the following paragraph shall be inserted:--`
  line
  line `"vi-A. In suits for partition and separate possession of a share of joint family property or of joint`
  line `property, or to enforce a right to a share in any property on the ground that it is joint family property`
  line `or joint property--`
  line
  line `if the plaintiff alleges that he has been excluded from possession of the property of which he`
  line `claims to be a coparcener or co-owner-according to the market-value of the share in respect of which`
  line `the suit is instituted.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The word "possession" for the purposes of this paragraph includes constructive`
  line `possession."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 10]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of section 7 of Act 7 of 1870.-- In section 7 of the Court Fees Act, 1870 (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the principal Act),--`
  line
  line '(a) in the first proviso to clause (iv), for the words thirteen rupees, the words `twenty-five'
  line `rupees' shall be substituted ; and`
  line
  line `(b) for clause (v), the following clause shall be substituted, namely :--`
  line
  line `"(v) in suits for the possession of land, houses and gardens, according to the value of the`
  line `subject matter ; and such value shall be deemed to be,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the subject matter is land, according to the market value thereof which shall be`
  line `deemed to be,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of land which is irrigated by perennial canal, two thousand rupees per`
  line `acre ;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of land which is irrigated by non-perennial canal or by well, one`
  line `thousand and five hundred rupees per acre ;`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of land which is Barani, one thousand rupees per acre ;`
  line
  line `(iv) in the case of land which is Sailab or Bhud, seven hundred and fifty rupees per`
  line `acre ; and`
  line
  line `(v) in the case of land which is Thur, Sem, Banjar or of like nature, five hundred`
  line `rupees per acre ; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the subject matter is house or garden, according to its market value ;".`
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 11 of 1974, s. 2]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of section 7 of Act 7 of 1870.--In section 7 of the Court Fees Act, 1870 (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the principal Act), for sub-clauses (a) and (b) of clause (r), the (following sub-clauses shall`
  line `be substituted, namely :--`
  line
  line `"(a) where the subject matter is land other than land situated within municipal limits or Abadi`
  line `Deh whether under cultivation or not according to the market value thereof which shall be deemed to`
  line be,--
  line
  line `(i) in the case of land which is irrigated by perennial canal, sixty rupees per acre ;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of land which is irrigated by non-perennial canal or by well, fifty rupees per`
  line `acre ; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of land which is Barani, Sailab, Bhud, Thur, Sem, Banjar or of like nature,`
  line `thirty rupees per acre ; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the subject matter is house, garden, or land situated within municipal limits or Abadi`
  line `Deh whether under cultivation or not, according to its market value ; ",`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 22 of 1974, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, section thirty-one, shall apply as if, for the word claim, the`
  line `words relief sought, were substituted omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 3 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. See para.8 of the A.O. 1937. In view of this provision the expression Governor of Bombay in Council has been left`
  line unmodified.
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 6 of 1905, s. 2.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for land`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (46661)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Fee on memorandum of appeal against order relating to compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46661&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The amount of`
  line `fee payable under this Act on a memorandum of appeal against an order relating to compensation`
  line `under any Act for the time being in force for the ^1acquisition of land for public purposes, shall be`
  line `computed according to the difference between the amount awarded and the amount claimed by`
  line `the appellant.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 8A in Act (7 of 1870).--After section 8 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted:--`
  line
  line `"8A. Statement of particulars of subject-matters of suits and plaintiffs valuation thereof.--In`
  line `every suit in which an advalorem court-fee is payable under this Act on the plaint, the plaintiff shall file`
  line `with the plaint a statement of particulars of the subject-matter of the suit ad his own valuation thereof`
  line `unless such particulars and the valuation are contained in the plaint. The statement shall be in such form`
  line `and shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed by the Provincial Government by notification in`
  line `the Gazette. In every such suit the plaintiff shall also, if the Court so directs, file a duplicate copy of the`
  line `plaint and of the said statement".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 11]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of section 8 of central Act 7 of 1870.--To section 8 of the Court Fees Act, 1870,`
  line `(hereinafter called the principal Act), the following proviso, shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Provided that the fixed court fee of one hundred rupees shall be payable on the memorandum of a`
  line `appeal or cross objections before the High Court arising under the Land Acquisition Act, 1984 or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force for acquisition of land for public purposes.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 3 of 1990, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46662)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to ascertain net profits or market-value.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46662&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `If the Court sees reason to think that the`
  line `annual nett profits or the market-value of any such land, house or garden as is mentioned in section 7,`
  line `paragraphs (v) and (vi), have or has been wrongly estimated, the Court may, for the purpose of computing`
  line `the fee payable in any suit therein mentioned, issue a commission to any proper person directing him to`
  line `make such local or other investigation as may be necessary, and to report thereon to the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46663)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Procedure where net profits or market-value wrongly estimated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (iii) rep. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 3 and the First Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46663&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(i) If in the result`
  line `of any such investigation the Court finals that the nett profits or market-value have or has been`
  line `wrongly estimated, the Court, if the estimation has been excessive, may in its discretion refund`
  line `the excess paid as such fee: but, if the estimation has been insufficient, the Court shall require`
  line `the plaintiff to pay so much additional fee as would have been payable had the said market-value`
  line `or nett profits been rightly estimated.`
  line
  line `(ii) In such case the suit shall be stayed until the additional fee is paid. If the additional fee is not paid`
  line `within such time as the Court shall fix, the suit shall be dismissed.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46819)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Procedure in suits for mesne profits or account when amount decreed exceeds amount claimed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46819&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `In suits for mesne profits or for immovable property and mesne profits, or for an account, if the profits or amount decreed are or is in excess of the profits claimed or the amount at which the plaintiff`
  line `valued the relief sought, the decree shall not be executed until the difference between the fee actually paid`
  line `and the fee which would have been payable had the suit comprised the whole of the profits or amount so`
  line `decreed shall have been paid to the proper officer.`
  line
  line `Where the amount of mesne profits is left to be ascertained in the course of the execution of the`
  line `decree, if the profits so ascertained exceed the profits claimed, the further execution of the decree shall be`
  line `stayed until the difference between the fee actually paid and the fee which would have been payable had`
  line `the suit comprised the whole of the profits so ascertained is paid. If the additional fee is not paid within`
  line `such time as the Court shall fix, the suit shall be dismissed.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 11 of Act (7 of 1870).--For the second paragraph of section 11 of the`
  line `principal Act the following paragraphs shall be substituted:--`
  line
  line `"Where a decree directs an enquiry as to mesne-profits which have accrued on the property`
  line `during a period prior to the institution of the suit, if the profits ascertained on such inquiry exceed the`
  line `profits claimed, no final decree shall be passed till the difference between the fee actually paid and`
  line `the fee which would have been payable had the suit comprised the whole of the profits so ascertained`
  line `is paid. If the additional fee is not paid within such time as the Court shall fix, the claim for the excess`
  line `shall be dismissed, unless the Court, for sufficient cause, extends the time for payment.`
  line
  line `Where a decree directs an inquiry as to mesno-profits from the institution of the suit and a final`
  line `decree is passed in accordance with the result of such inquiry , the decree shall not be executed until`
  line `such fee is paid would have been payable on the amount claimed in execution if a separate suit had`
  line `been instituted therefor."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 12]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46665)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Decision of questions as to valuation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46665&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(i) Every question relating to valuation for the purpose`
  line `of determining the amount of any fee chargeable under this Chapter on a plaint or memorandum of`
  line `appeal, shall be decided by the Court in which such plaint or memorandum, as the case may be, is filed,`
  line `and such decision shall be final as between the parties to the suit.`
  line
  line `(ii) But whenever any such suit comes before a Court of appeal, reference or revision, if such Court`
  line `considers that the said question has been wrongly decided to the detriment of the revenue, it shall require`
  line `the party by whom such fee has been paid to pay so much additional fee as would have been payable had`
  line `the question been rightly decided, and the provisions of section 10, paragraph (ii), shall apply.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 12 of Act (7 of 1870).-- (1) In section 12 of the principal Act, for paragraph`
  line `ii, the following paragraph shall be substituted:--`
  line
  line `"ii. But whenever any such suit comes before a Court of appeal, reference or revision, if such`
  line `Court considers that the said question has been wrongly decided, it shall--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case in which the decision is to the detriment of revenue, require the party by`
  line `whom such fee has been paid, to pay so much additional fee as would have been payable had the`
  line `question been rightly decided and thereafter--`
  line
  line `(i) if the party required to pay is the appellant or petitioner, the appeal or petition shall be`
  line `stayed until the additional fee is paid. If the additional fee is not paid within such time as the`
  line `Court shall fix, the appeal or petition shall be dismissed;`
  line
  line `(ii) if the party required to pay it‘s the respondent or the opposite party, the Court shall`
  line `fix a date before which such party shall pay the amount of court fee due from him and, if`
  line `such party fails to pay the fee required before the date fixed by the Court, the Court shall`
  line `recover the amount of such fee from him as if it were an arrear of land revenue. Where the`
  line `Court considers that the amount of such fee should be paid to the respondent or the opposite party by the appellant or the petitioner, as the case may be , the Court may provide for such`
  line `payment in the order as to costs in the said appeal or petition; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any case in which the decision is that any excess fee has been levied, direct the refund of`
  line `so much excess fee to the party who paid it as would not have been payable had the question been`
  line `rightly decided.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section a question relating to the classification of any suit`
  line `in regard to section 7 shall not be deemed to be a question relating to valuation."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 13]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46666)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Refund of fee paid on memorandum of appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46666&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `If an appeal or plaint, which has been`
  line `rejected by the lower Court on any of the grounds mentioned in the ^1Code of Civil Procedure, is ordered`
  line `to be received, or if a suit is remanded in appeal, on any of the grounds mentioned in ^2`
  line `section 351 of the`
  line `same Code, for a second decision by the lower Court, the Appellate Court shall grant to the appellant a`
  line `certificate, authorizing him to receive back from the Collector the full amount of fee paid on the`
  line `memorandum of appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, in the case of a remand in appeal, the order of remand shall not cover the whole of`
  line `the subject-matter of the suit, the certificate so granted shall not authorize the appellant to receive back`
  line `more than so much fee as would have been originally payable on the part or parts of such subject-matter`
  line `in respect whereof the suit has been remanded.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 13.--In the Court-fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870),--`
  line
  line `(a) For the marginal heading to section 13, the following marginal heading shall be substituted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"Refund of fee paid on memorandum of appeal and in cases where compromise or settlement has`
  line `been arrived at by a Lok Adalat.";`
  line
  line `(b) Section 13 shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof and --`
  line
  line `(i) In sub-section (1) as so renumbered, for the words and figures " the Code of Civil Procedure"`
  line `and "section 351 of the same Code", the words and figures " the Code Civil Procedure, 1908" and`
  line `"rule 23 of Order XLI of the First Schedule to the said Code" shall respectively be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(ii) After sub-section (1) as so renumbered, the following new sub-section shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) Where a compromise or settlement has been arrived at, by a Lok Adalat in a case`
  line `referred to it under sub-section (1) of section 20 of the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39`
  line `of 1987), the Court by which the case was so referred to the Lok Adalat shall grant a certificate`
  line `to the party or every party to the case who paid any court-fee in that case, authorizing him to`
  line `receive back from the Collector the full amount of the fee so paid.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 7 of 2002, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `2. This reference should now be read as applying to the corresponding provision of Act 5 of 1908, i.e., Order XLI, rule 23 of the`
  line `First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46667)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Refund of fee on application for review of judgment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46667&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where an ^1`
  line `application for a review of`
  line `judgment is presented on or after the ninetieth day from the date of the decree, the Court, unless the delay`
  line `was caused by the applicant's laches, may, in its discretion, grant him a certificate authorizing him to`
  line `receive back from the Collector so much of the fee paid on the application as exceeds the fee which`
  line `would have been payable had it been presented before ^2`
  line `such day.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. As to application for review of judgment, see the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908), s. 114 and Order`
  line `XLVII of the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. See the First Schedule, Nos. 4 and 5, infra.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46668)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Refund where Court reverses or modifies its former decision on ground of mistake.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1870, s. 1, for "plaint or memorandum of appeal".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46668&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Refund where Court reverses or modifies its former decision on ground of mistake.`
  line `Where an application for a review of judgment is admitted, and where, on the rehearing, the`
  line `Court reverses or modifies its former decision on the ground of mistake in law or fact, the`
  line `applicant shall be entitled to a certificate from the Court authorising him to receive back from`
  line `the Collector so much of the fee paid on the ^1[application] as exceeds the fee payable on any`
  line `other application to such Court under the second schedule to this Act, No. 1, clause (b) or clause`
  line `(d).`
  line
  line `But nothing in the former part of this section shall entitle the applicant to such certificate`
  line `where the reversal or modification is due, wholly or in part, to fresh evidence which might have`
  line `been produced at the original hearing.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46669)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Refund of fee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
