  line `[Additional fee where respondent takes objection to un-appealed part of decree.] Rep. by the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (46670)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Multifarious suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46670&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Where a suit embraces two or more distinct subjects, the plaint or`
  line `memorandum of appeal shall be chargeable with the aggregate amount of the fees to which the`
  line `plaints or memoranda of appeal in suits embracing separately each of such subjects would be`
  line `liable under this Act.`
  line `Nothing in the former part of this section shall be deemed to affect the power conferred by the ^1Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure, section 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (46671)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Written examinations of complainants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46671&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `When the first or only examination of a person`
  line `who complains of the offence of wrongful confinement, or of wrongful restraint, or of any offence other`
  line `than an offence for which police-officers may arrest without a warrant, and who has not already presented`
  line `a petition on which a fee has been levied under this Act, is reduced to writing under the provisions of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, the complainant shall pay a fee of eight annas, unless the Court thinks fit to`
  line `remit such payment.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 18 of Act (7 of 1870).--In section 18 of the principal Act, for the words`
  line `"eight annas" the words "one rupee" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 14]`
  line
  line `Insertion of a new section 18-A Act (7 of 1l870).--After section 18 of the Court Fees Act, 1870, as`
  line `in force in the State of Orissa the following new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"18-A. Exemption to women.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act no plaint in`
  line `respect of a suit filed by a women, whose annual income does not exceed three thousand rupees, for`
  line `maintenance or for enhancement of maintenance or for recovery of share in the estate of her deceased`
  line `husband or parent in the family property and no petitions filed by any such women for divorce on`
  line `ground of cruelty or other misconduct on the part of her husband shall be chargeable with court fees.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court in which such plaint or petition is filed shall have power to make such inquiry as it`
  line `deems fit for assessing the income of the plaintiff or the petitioner, as the case may be.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 55 of 1975, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (46672)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Exemption of certain documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46672&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall render the following`
  line `documents chargeable with any fee:`
  line
  line `(i) Power-of-attorney to institute or defend a suit when executed ^1`
  line `[by a member of any of the`
  line `Armed Forces of the Union] not in civil employment.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(iii) Written statements called for by the Court after the first hearing of a suit.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(v) Plaints in suits tried by ^4`
  line `village Munsifs in the Presidency of Fort St. George.`
  line
  line `(vi) Plaints and processes in suits before District Panchayats in the same residency.`
  line
  line `(vii) Plaints in suits before Collectors under Madras Regulation 12 of 1816.`
  line
  line `(viii) Probate of a will, letters of administration, ^5`
  line `[and, save as regards debts and securities a`
  line `certificate under Bombay Regulation 8 of 1827], where the amount or value of the property in respect`
  line `of which the probate or letters or certificate shall be granted does not exceed one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(ix) Application or petition to a Collector or other officer making a settlement of land-revenue, or`
  line `to a Board of Revenue, or a Commissioner of Revenue, relating to matters connected with the`
  line `assessment of land or the ascertainment of rights thereto or interests therein, if presented previous to`
  line `the final confirmation of such settlement.`
  line
  line `(x) Application relating to a supply for irrigation of water belonging to Government.`
  line
  line `(xi) Application for leave to extend cultivation, or to relinquish land, when presented to an officer`
  line `of land-revenue by a person holding, under direct engagement with Government, land of which the`
  line `revenue is settled, but not permanently.`
  line
  line `(xii) Application for service of notice of relinquishment of land or of enhancement of rent.`
  line
  line `(xiii) Written authority to an agent to distrain.`
  line
  line `(xiv) First application (other than a petition containing a criminal charge or information)`
  line `for the summons of a witness or other person to attend either to give evidence or to produce a document or in respect of the production or filing of an exhibit not being an affidavit made for`
  line `the immediate purpose of being produced in Court.`
  line
  line `(xv) Bail-bonds in criminal cases, recognizances to prosecute or give evidence, and recognizances`
  line `for personal appearance or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(xvi) Petition, application, charge or information respecting any offence when presented,`
  line `made or laid to or before a police-officer, or to or before the ^6Heads of Villages or the ^7Village`
  line `Police in the territories respectively subject to the Governors in Council of Madras and`
  line Bombay.
  line
  line `(xvii) Petition by a prisoner, or other person in duress or under restraint of any Court or its`
  line officers.
  line
  line `(xviii) Complaint of a public servant [as defined in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860)], a`
  line `municipal officer, or an officer or servant of a Railway Company.`
  line
  line `(xix) Application for permission to cut timber in Government forests, or otherwise relating to`
  line `such forests.`
  line
  line `(xx) Application for the payment of money due by Government to the applicant.`
  line
  line `(xxi) Petition of appeal against the chaukidari assessment under ^8Act No. 20 of 1856, or against`
  line `any municipal tax.`
  line
  line `(xxii) Applications for compensation under any law for the time being in force relating to the`
  line ^9
  line `acquisition of property for public purposes.`
  line
  line `(xxiii) Petitions presented to the Special Commissioner appointed under ^10Bengal Act No. 2 of`
  line `1869 (to ascertain, regulate and record certain tenures in Chota Nagpur.).`
  line
  line [
  line ^11
  line `(xxiv) (Petitions under the Indian Christian Marriage Act, 1872 (15 of 1872), sections 45 and`
  line 48.]
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `In section 19 of the Court-Fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870) (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act) in`
  line `clause (viii) for the words" one thousand rupees" the words "two thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 11 of 1967, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for by an officer, warrant-officer, non-commissioned officer or private of Her Majesty's army.`
  line
  line `2. Clause (ii) rep. by s. Act 12 of 1891, s. 3 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Clause (iv) rep. by Act 13 of 1889, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `4. See the Madras Village Courts Act, 1889 (Mad. 1 of 1889).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 7 of 1889, s. 13, for and certificate mentioned in the first schedule to this Act annexed, No. 12.`
  line
  line `6. See Madras Regulations 11 of 1816 and 4 of 1821, s. 6.`
  line
  line `7. See Bombay Village Police Act, 1867 (Born. 8 of 1867), ss. 14, 15 and 16.`
  line
  line `8. The Bengal Chaukidari Act, 1856.`
  line
  line `9. See now the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
  line
  line `10. The Chota Nagpur Tenures Act, 1869.`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 15 of 1872, s. 2, for clause (xiv) which read as follows:---`
  line
  line `Petitions under the 14th and 15th of Victoria, Ch. 40 (an Act for marriages in India), s. 5, or under Act No. 5 of 1852, s. 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (46673)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 21
  title `Relief where too high a court-fee has been paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46673&sectionno=19A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[19A. Relief where too high a court-fee has been paid.-- Where any person on applying for`
  line `the probate of a will or letters of administration has estimated the property of the deceased to be of`
  line `greater value than the same has afterwards proved to be, and has consequently paid too high a`
  line `court-fee thereon, if, within six months after the true value of the property has been ascertained,`
  line `such person produces the probate or letters to the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority^2[for the`
  line `local area] in which the probate or letters has or have been granted,`
  line
  line `and delivers to such Authority a particular inventory and valuation of the property of the deceased,`
  line `verified by affidavit or affirmation,`
  line
  line `and if such Authority is satisfied that a greater fee was paid on the probate or letters than the law`
  line required,
  line
  line `the said Authority may`
  line
  line `(a) cancel the stamp on the probate or letters if such stamp has not been already cancelled;`
  line
  line `(b) substitute another stamp for denoting the court-fee which should have been thereon; and`
  line
  line `(c) make an allowance for the difference between them as in the case of spoiled stamps, or repay`
  line `the same in money, at his discretion.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1875, s. 6.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 1901, s. 3, for "of the Province".`
obj_root_law_sections_19_b:
  sectionId (46674)
  sectionNo 19B
  orderNo 22
  title `Relief where debts due from a deceased person have been paid out of his estate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1875, s. 6.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46674&sectionno=19B&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[19B. Relief where debts due from a deceased person have been paid out of his estate.-- Whenever it is proved to the satisfaction of such Authority that an executor or administrator has`
  line `paid debts due from the deceased to such an amount as, being deducted out of the amount or value`
  line `of the estate, reduces the same to a sum which, if it had been the whole gross amount or value of the`
  line `estate, would have occasioned a less court-fee to be paid on the probate or letters of administration`
  line `granted in respect of such estate than has been actually paid thereon under this Act,`
  line
  line `such Authority may return the difference, provided the same be claimed within three years after the`
  line `date of such probate or letters.`
  line
  line `But when by reason of any legal proceeding, the debts due from the deceased have not been`
  line `ascertained and paid, or his effects have not been recovered and made available, and in consequence`
  line `thereof the executor or administrator is prevented from claiming the return of such difference within`
  line `the said term of three years, the said Authority may allow such further time for making the claim as`
  line `may appear to be reasonable under the circumstances.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_c:
  sectionId (46675)
  sectionNo 19C
  orderNo 23
  title `Relief in case of several grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46675&sectionno=19C&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[19C. Relief in case of several grants.-- Whenever ^2*** a grant of probate or letters of`
  line `administration has been or is made in respect of the whole of the property belonging to an estate,`
  line `and the full fee chargeable under this Act has been or is paid thereon, no fee shall be chargeable`
  line `under the same Act when a like grant is made in respect of the whole or any part of the same`
  line `property belonging to the same estate.`
  line
  line `Whenever such a grant has been or is made in respect of any property forming part of an`
  line `estate, the amount of fees then actually paid under this Act shall be deducted when a like grant is`
  line `made in respect of property belonging to the same estate, identical with or including the property`
  line `to which the former grant relates.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1875, s. 6.`
  line
  line `2. The word "such" rep. by Act 12 of 1891.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_d:
  sectionId (46676)
  sectionNo 19D
  orderNo 24
  title `Probates declared valid as to trust-property though not covered by court-fee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1875, s. 6.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46676&sectionno=19D&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[19D. Probates declared valid as to trust property though not covered by court-fee.-- The`
  line `probate of the will or the letters of administration of the effects of any person deceased heretofore or`
  line `hereafter granted shall be deemed valid and available by his executors or administrators for`
  line `recovering, transferring or assigning, any movable or immovable property whereof or whereto the`
  line `deceased was possessed or entitled, either wholly or partially as a trustee, notwithstanding the amount`
  line `or value of such property is not included in the amount or value of the estate in respect of which a`
  line `court-fee was paid on such probate or letters of administration.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_e:
  sectionId (46677)
  sectionNo 19E
  orderNo 25
  title `Provision for case where too low a court-fee has been paid on probates, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46677&sectionno=19E&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[19E. Provision for case where too low a court-fee has been paid on probates, etc.-- Where`
  line `any person on applying for probate or letters of administration has estimated the estate of the`
  line `deceased to be of less value than the same has afterwards proved to be, and has in consequence`
  line `paid too low a court-fee thereon, the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority ^2[for the local area] in`
  line `which the probate or letters has or have been granted may, on the value of the estate of the`
  line `deceased being verified by affidavit or affirmation, cause the probate or letters of administration to`
  line `be duly stamped on payment of the full court-fee which ought to have been originally paid thereon`
  line `in respect of such value and of the further penalty, if the probate or letters is or are produced`
  line `within one year from the date of grant, of five times, or, if it or they is or are produced after one`
  line `year from such date, of twenty times, such proper court-fee, without any deduction of the court-fee`
  line `originally paid on such probate or letters:]`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the application be made within six months after the ascertainment of the true`
  line `value of the estate and the discovery that too low a court-fee was at first paid on the probate or`
  line `letters, and if the said Authority is satisfied that such fee was paid in consequence of a mistake or`
  line `of its not being known at the time that some particular part of the estate belonged to the deceased, and without any intention of fraud or to delay the payment of the proper court-fee, the said Authority may`
  line `remit the said penalty, and cause the probate or letters to be duly stamped on payment only of the sum`
  line `wanting to make up the fee which should have been at first paid thereon.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1875, s. 6.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 1901, s. 3, for "of the Province".`
obj_root_law_sections_19_f:
  sectionId (46678)
  sectionNo 19F
  orderNo 26
  title `Administrator to give proper security before letters stamped under section.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1875, s. 6.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46678&sectionno=19F&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[19F. Administrator to give proper security before letters stamped under section 19E.-- In case`
  line `of letters of administration on which too low a court-fee has been paid at first, the said Authority shall not`
  line `cause the same to be duly stamped in manner aforesaid until the administrator has given such security to`
  line `the Court by which the letters of administration have been granted as ought by law to have been given on`
  line `the granting thereof in case the full value of the estate of the deceased had been then ascertained.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_g:
  sectionId (46820)
  sectionNo 19G
  orderNo 27
  title `Executors, etc., not paying full court-fee on probates, etc., within six months after discovery of underpayment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_g_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_g_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46820&sectionno=19G&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_g_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[19G. Executors, etc., not paying full court-fee on probates, etc., within six months`
  line `after discovery of under-payment.—Where too low a court-fee has been paid on any probate or`
  line `letters of administration in consequence of any mistake, or of its not being known at the time that some`
  line `particular part of the estate belonged to the deceased, if any executor or administrator acting under such`
  line `probate or letters does not, within six months ^2`
  line `*** after the discovery of the mistake or of any effects not`
  line `known at the time to have belonged to the deceased, apply to the said Authority and pay what is wanting`
  line `to make up the court-fee which ought to have been paid at first on such probate or letters, he shall forfeit`
  line `the sum of one thousand rupees and also a further sum at the rate of ten per cent. on the amount of the`
  line `sum wanting to make up the proper court-fee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_g_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. As to recovery of penalties or forfeitures under s. 19G, see s. 19J, infra.`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures "after the first day of April, 1875, or "rep. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 3 and the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_h:
  sectionId (46821)
  sectionNo 19H
  orderNo 28
  title `Notice of applications for probate or letters of administration to be given to Revenueauthorities, and procedure thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46821&sectionno=19H&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_h_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[19H. Notice of applications for probate or letters of administration to be given to Revenue`
  line `authorities, and procedure thereon.—(1) Where an application for probate or letters of administration`
  line `is made to any Court other than a High Court, the Court shall cause notice of the application to be given`
  line `to the Collector.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such an application as aforesaid is made to a High Court, the High Court shall cause`
  line `notice of the application to be given to the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority ^2`
  line `[for the local area in`
  line `which the High Court is situated].`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector within the local limits of whose revenue-jurisdiction the property of the deceased`
  line `or any part thereof is, may at any time inspect or cause to be inspected, and take or cause to be taken`
  line `copies of, the record of any case in which application for probate or letters of administration has been`
  line `made; and if, on such inspection or otherwise, he is of opinion that the petitioner has under-estimated the`
  line `value of the property of the deceased, the Collector may, if he thinks fit, require the attendance of the`
  line `petitioner (either in person or by agent) and take evidence and inquire into the matter in such manner as`
  line `he may think fit, and, if he is still of opinion that the value of the property has been under-estimated, may`
  line `require the petitioner to amend the valuation.`
  line
  line `(4) If the petitioner does not amend the valuation to the satisfaction of the Collector, the Collector`
  line `may move the Court before which the application for probate or letters of administration was made, to`
  line `hold an inquiry into the true value of the property:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such motion shall be made after the expiration of six months from the date of the`
  line `exhibition of the inventory required by section 277 of the ^3`
  line `Indian Succession Act, 1865 (10 of 1865), or`
  line `as the case may be, by section 98 of the ^3`
  line `Probate and Administration Act, 1881 (5 of 1881).`
  line
  line `(5) The Court, when so moved as aforesaid, shall hold, or cause to be held, an inquiry accordingly,`
  line `and shall record a finding as to the true value, as near as may be, at which the property of the deceased`
  line `should have been estimated. The Collector shall be deemed to be a party to the inquiry.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purposes of any such inquiry, the Court or person authorised by the Court to`
  line `hold the inquiry may examine the petitioner for probate or letters of administration on oath`
  line `(whether in person or by commission), and may take such further evidence as may be produced to prove the true value of the property. The person authorised as aforesaid to hold the inquiry shall return`
  line `to the Court the evidence taken by him and report the result of the inquiry, and such report and the`
  line `evidence so taken shall be evidence in the proceeding, and the Court may record a finding in accordance`
  line `with the report, unless it is satisfied that it is erroneous.`
  line
  line `(7) The finding of the Court recorded under sub-section (5) shall be final, but shall not bar the`
  line `entertainment and disposal by the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority of any application under`
  line `section 19E.`
  line
  line `(8) The State Government may make rules for the guidance of Collectors in the exercise of the`
  line `powers conferred by sub-section (3).]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_h_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1899, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 1901, s. 3, for "of the Province".`
  line
  line `3. See now the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_i:
  sectionId (46822)
  sectionNo 19-I
  orderNo 29
  title `Payment of court-fees in respect of probates and letters of administration`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1899, s 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46822&sectionno=19-I&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_i_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[19-I. Payment of court-fees in respect of probates and letters of administration.—(1) No order`
  line `entitling the petitioner to the grant of probate or letters of administration shall be made upon an`
  line `application for such grant until the petitioner has filed in the Court a valuation of the property in the form`
  line `set forth in the third schedule, and the Court is satisfied that the fee mentioned in No. 11 of the first`
  line `schedule has been paid on such valuation.`
  line
  line `(2) The grant of probate or letters of administration shall not be delayed by reason of any motion`
  line `made by the Collector under section 19H, sub-section (4).]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_j:
  sectionId (46681)
  sectionNo 19J
  orderNo 30
  title `Recovery of penalties, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_j_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_j_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46681&sectionno=19J&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[19J. Recovery of penalties, etc.-- (1) Any excess fee found to be payable on any inquiry held`
  line `under section 19H, sub-section (6), and any penalty or forfeiture under section 19G, may, on the`
  line `certificate of the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority, be recovered from the executor or administrator as`
  line `if it were an arrear of land-revenue by any Collector ^2***.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Controlling Revenue-authority may remit the whole or any part of any such penalty or`
  line `forfeiture as aforesaid, or any part of any penalty under section 19E or of any court-fee under section 19E`
  line `in excess of the full court-fee which ought to have been paid.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_j_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1899, s 2.`
  line
  line `2. The words "in any part of British India" rep by the A.O. 1948.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_k:
  sectionId (46682)
  sectionNo 19K
  orderNo 31
  title `Sections 6 and 28 not to apply to probates or letters of administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_k_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1899, s 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46682&sectionno=19K&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_19_k_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[19K. Sections 6 and 28 not to apply to probates or letters of administration.—Nothing in`
  line `section 6 or section 28 shall apply to probates or letters of administration.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (46684)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 32
  title `Rules as to cost of processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46684&sectionno=20&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The High Court shall, as soon as may be, make rules as to the`
  line `following matters:—`
  line
  line `(i) The fees chargeable for serving and executing processes issued by such court in its appellate`
  line `jurisdiction, and by the other Civil and Revenue Courts established within the local limits of such`
  line jurisdiction;
  line
  line `(ii) the fees chargeable for serving and executing processes issued by the Criminal Courts established`
  line `within such limits in the case of offences other than offences for which police-officers may arrest without`
  line `a warrant; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the remuneration of the peons and all other persons employed by leave of a Court in the service`
  line `or execution of processes.`
  line
  line `The High Court may from time to time alter and add to the rules so made.`
  line
  line `Confirmation and publication of rules.—All such rules, alterations and additions shall,`
  line `after being confirmed by the State Government ^1`
  line `***, be published in the Official Gazette, and`
  line `shall thereupon have the force of law.`
  line
  line `Until such rules shall be so made and published, the fees now leviable for serving and executing`
  line `processes shall continue to be levied, and shall be deemed to be fees leviable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and sanctioned by the Governor General of India in Council" omitted by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (46685)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 33
  title `Tables of process-fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46685&sectionno=21&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `A table in the English and Vernacular languages, showing`
  line `the fees chargeable for such service and execution, shall be exposed to view in a conspicuous`
  line `part of each Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (46686)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 34
  title `Number of peons in District and subordinate Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46686&sectionno=22&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Subject to rules to be made by the High`
  line `Court and approved by the State Government ^1***,`
  line
  line `every District Judge and every Magistrate of a district shall fix, and may from time to time alter, the`
  line `number of peons necessary to be employed for the service and execution of processes issued out of his`
  line `Court and each of the Courts subordinate thereto,`
  line
  line `Number of peons in Mufassal Small Cause Courts.-- aand for the purposes of this section,`
  line `every Court of Small Causes established under Act No. 11 of 1865 (to consolidate and amend`
  line `the law relating to Courts of Small Causes beyond the local limits of the ordinary original civil`
  line `jurisdiction of the High Courts of Judicature)^2 shall be deemed to be subordinate to the Court of`
  line `the District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and the Governor General of India in Council" omitted by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. The reference to Act 11 of 1865 should now be read as referring to the Provincial Small Cause Courts Act, 1887 (9 of 1887);`
  line `see s. 2(3) of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (46687)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 35
  title `Number of peons in Revenue Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. The words "and the Governor General of India in Council" omitted by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46687&sectionno=23&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Subject to rules to be framed by the Chief`
  line `Controlling Revenue-authority and approved by the State Government ^1***, every officer`
  line `performing the functions of a Collector of a district shall fix, and may from time to time alter,`
  line `the number of peons necessary to be employed for the service and execution of processes issued`
  line `out of his Court or the courts subordinate to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (46688)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 36
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46688&sectionno=24&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `[Process served under this Chapter to be held to be process within meaning of Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure.] by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1891 (12 of 1891), s. 3 and`
  line `the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Substitution of section 24-A.--For section 24-A for the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"24-A. Control of Court fee and Stamp Commissioner.--(1) The levy of fees under this Act shall`
  line `be under the general control and superintendence of the Chief Controlling Revenue Authority, who may`
  line `be assisted in the supervision thereof by the Commissioner of Stamps and by as many Additional many`
  line `Additional Commissioners of the Stamps, Deputy Commissioners of Stamps and Assistant`
  line `Commissioners of Stamps as the State Government may appoint in the behalf or by any other subordinate`
  line `agency appointed for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The Officers and the agency referred to in sub-section (1) shall have access to all records, and`
  line `shall be furnished with all such information as may be required by them for the performance of their`
  line `duties under this Act."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 6 of 1980, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (46689)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 37
  title `Collection of fees by stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46689&sectionno=25&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `All fees referred to in section 3 or chargeable under this Act shall`
  line `be collected by stamps.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (46690)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 38
  title `Stamps to be impressed or adhesive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46690&sectionno=26&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The stamps used to denote any fees chargeable under`
  line `this Act shall be impressed or adhesive, or pertly impressed and partly adhesive, as the ^1`
  line [appropriate
  line `Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, from time to time direct^2.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir (UT).--`
  line
  line `Section 26 shall be numbered as sub-section (1) thereof, and after sub-section (1) so renumbered,`
  line `insert the following sub-section, namely:--`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), and section 25, "stamp" means any mark, seal or endorsement`
  line `by any agency or person duly authorised by the Appropriate Government, and includes an adhesive or`
  line `impressed stamp, for the purposes of court fee chargeable under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation:--"impressed stamp" includes impression by a franking machine or another machine, or a`
  line `unique number generated by e-stamping or similar software, as the Appropriate Government may, by`
  line `notification in the official Gazette, specify".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No.`
  line `S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020).]`
  line
  line `Union Territory of Ladakh`
  line
  line `Section 26.--Numbered as sub-section (1) thereof, and after sub-section (1) as so numbered,`
  line insert-
  line
  line `'(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), and section 25, "stamp" means any mark, seal or`
  line `endorsement by any agency or person duly authorised by the Appropriate Government, and includes`
  line `an adhesive or impressed stamp, for the purposes of court fee chargeable under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation 7.--The expression "impressed stamp" includes impression by a franking machine or`
  line `another machine, or a unique number generated by e-stamping or similar software, as the Appropriate`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.'.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--The expression "e-stamping" means stamping using unique number or code`
  line `through an electronic machine or a software application'.`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, Notification`
  line `No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of section 26 of Central Act 7 of 1870.--In section 26 of the Court Fees act, 1870, the`
  line `following explanation shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "stamp" means any mark, seal or endorsement by any agency or person duly authorized by`
  line `the State Government and includes and adhesive or impressed stamp chargeable for the purposes`
  line `of court fee under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(ii) "impressed stamp" means an impression by a franking or any other machine, or estamping.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 29 of 2016, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L. G.".`
  line
  line `2. For rules as to levy of court-fees by adhesive and impressed stamps, see Gazette of India, 1883. Pt. I., p 189.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (46691)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 39
  title `Rules for supply, number, renewal and keeping accounts of stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L. G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46691&sectionno=27&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[appropriate`
  line `Government] may, from time to time, make rules for regulating—`
  line
  line `(a) the supply of stamps to be used under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of stamps to be used for denoting any fee chargeable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the renewal of damaged or spoiled stamps; and`
  line
  line `(d) the keeping accounts of all stamps used under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of stamps used under section 3 in a High Court, such rules shall be made`
  line `with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of such Court.`
  line
  line `All such rules shall be published in the Official Gazette, and shall thereupon have the force`
  line `of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (46692)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 40
  title `Stamping documents inadvertently received.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46692&sectionno=28&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No document which ought to bear a stamp`
  line `under this Act shall be of any validity, unless and until it is properly stamped.`
  line
  line `But, if any such document is through mistake or inadvertence received, filed or used in any Court or`
  line `office without being properly stamped, the presiding Judge or the head of the office, as the case may be,`
  line `or, in the case of a High Court, any Judge of such Court, may, if he thinks fit, order that such document be`
  line `stamped as he may direct; and, on such document being stamped accordingly, the same and every`
  line `proceeding relative thereto shall be as valid as if it had been properly stamped in the first instance.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion a new section 28-A, Act (7 of 1870).--After section 28 of the Court Fees Act, 1870 the`
  line `following new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"28-A. Deficient or unpaid court fees.--(1) If, on examination of the records of a Civil, Criminal or`
  line `Revenue case which has been disposed of, a public officer finds that the fee payable under the Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder on any document filed, exhibited or recorded therein has not been paid or has been insufficiently paid, he shall report the fact to the presiding officer of the Court or to the`
  line `revenue officer concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) Such presiding officer or revenue officer, after satisfying himself of the correctness of such`
  line `report, shall record a provisional finding that the proper fee has not been paid and determine the`
  line `amount of fee payable and the person from whom the fee or the difference thereof, if any, shall be`
  line recoverable.
  line
  line `(3) After recording a finding under sub-section (2), the presiding officer or revenue officer shall`
  line `issue a notice to the person referred to in that sub-section to show cause why he should not be ordered`
  line `to pay the fee determined thereunder, and , if sufficient cause is not shown, the presiding officer or`
  line `revenue officer shall confirm the finding and make an order requiring such person to pay the proper`
  line `fee before a date to be specified in that notice.`
  line
  line `(4) If such person fails to pay the fee in accordance with the notice issued under sub-section (3),`
  line `it shall on the certificate of such presiding officer or revenue officer, be recoverable as an arrear of`
  line `land revenue."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 13 of 1957, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (46693)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 41
  title `Amended document.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46693&sectionno=29&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Where any such document is amended in order merely to correct a`
  line `mistake and to make it conform to the original intention of the parties, it shall not be necessary to impose`
  line `a fresh stamp.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (46694)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 42
  title `Cancellation of stamp.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46694&sectionno=30&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No document requiring a stamp under this Act shall be filed or acted`
  line `upon in any proceeding in any Court or office until the stamp has been cancelled.`
  line
  line `Such officer as the Court or the head of the office may from time to time appoint shall, on`
  line `receiving any such document, forthwith effect such cancellation by punching out the figure-head`
  line `so as to leave the amount designated on the stamp untouched, and the part removed by punching`
  line `shall be burnt or otherwise destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (46695)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 43
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46695&sectionno=31&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `[Repayment of fees paid on applications to Criminal Courts.] Rep. by the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure (Amendment) Act, 1923 (18 of 1923), s. 163.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (46696)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 44
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46696&sectionno=32&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Amendment of Act 8 of 1859 and Act 9 of 1869. Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1891`
  line `(12 of 1891), s. 3 and the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (46697)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 45
  title `Admission in criminal cases of documents for which proper fee has not been paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46697&sectionno=33&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the filing or exhibition in a Criminal Court of a document in respect of which the proper fee`
  line `has not been paid is, in the opinion of the presiding Judge, necessary to prevent a failure of justice,`
  line `nothing contained in section 4 or section 6 shall be deemed to prohibit such filing or exhibition.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (46698)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 46
  title `Sale of stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46698&sectionno=34&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[34. Sale of stamps.(1) The ^2[appropriate Government] may from time to time make rules for`
  line `regulating the sale of stamps to be used under this Act, the persons by whom alone such sale is to be`
  line `conducted, and the duties and remuneration of such persons.`
  line
  line `(2) All such rules shall be published in the Official Gazette, and shall thereupon have the`
  line `force of law.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person appointed to sell stamps who disobeys any rule made under this section, and`
  line `any person not so appointed who sells or offers for sale any stamp, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five`
  line `hundred rupees, or, with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 3 and the First Schedule, for section 34.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for "L. G."`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (46699)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to reduce or remit fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46699&sectionno=35&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[appropriate Government] may, from time to time`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, reduce or remit, in the whole or in any part of ^2[the`
  line `territories; under its administration], all or any of the fees mentioned in the first and second`
  line `schedules to this Act annexed, and may in like manner cancel or vary such order.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 35 of Act (7 of 1870).--For section 35 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be substituted:--`
  line
  line `"35. Power to suspend, reduce or remit fees.--(1) The Provincial Government may from time`
  line `to time subject to such conditions or restrictions as it may think fit to impose, by notification in the`
  line `Gazette suspend the payment of or reduce or remit, in the whole of Orissa or in any part thereof, all or`
  line `any of the fees mentioned in Schedules I and II to this Act annexed and may in like manner cancel or`
  line `vary such order.`
  line
  line `(3) The Provincial Government may from time to time by rules prescribe the manner in which`
  line `any fee the payment of which is suspended under sub-section (1) may be realized and for this purpose`
  line `direct that such fee may be recovered as if it were an arrear of land revenue."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 1939, s. 15]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Substitution of section 35 of Central Act 7 of 1870.-- For section 35 of the Court Fees Act,`
  line `1870 (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), the following section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"35. Power to remit or reduce fees.--The State Government may, subject to such conditions or`
  line `restrictions as it may think fit to impose, by notification in the Official Gazette, reduce or remit in`
  line `relation to all or any class of persons, in the whole or any part of the territories under its`
  line `administration, all or any of the fees mentioned in the first and second schedules annexed to this Act`
  line `and may in like manner cancel or vary such order."`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 27 of 1976, s. 2]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Substitution of new Section for Section 35 of Act VII of 1870. -- For Section 35 of the said Act, the`
  line `following Section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"35. Power to remit or reduce Court-fees.---The State Government may, subject to such condition`
  line `or restriction as it may think fit to impose, by order published in the Official Gazette, reduce or`
  line `remit in relation to all or any class of persons, in the whole or any part of the State, all or any of`
  line `the fees mentioned in the First and Second Schedules to this Act and may in like manner cancel or`
  line `vary such order."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 20 of 1977, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for L. G..`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for British India.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (46700)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 48
  title `Saving of fees to certain officers of High Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465&sectionId=46700&sectionno=36&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00023_187007_1523268447465
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in Chapters II and V of this Act`
  line `applies to the commission payable to the Accountant General of the High Court at Fort William, or to the`
  line `fees which any officer of a High Court is allowed to receive in addition to a fixed salary.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Insertion of section 37 in Act 7 of 1870.-- After section 36 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely :--`
  line
  line `"37. Fees in High Court.--Nothing contained in Schedules I and II to this act shall apply`
  line `to the High Court of Punjab and Haryana and the provisions in that behalf applicable`
  line `immediately before the 1st day of November, 1966, shall continue to apply to the said High`
  line `Court.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 22 of 1974, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
